• Dynamic Blocks allow you to construct nested configuration blocks dynamically based on a list or map variable.
• Example: Creating multiple security rules inside an 'azurerm_network_security_group' resource based on a list of port numbers.
• Syntax:
  dynamic "security_rule" {
    for_each = var.rules
    content {
      name = security_rule.value.name
      port = security_rule.value.port
      # ... other attributes
    }
  }
• Best Practice: Use them to keep your code DRY (Don't Repeat Yourself) when dealing with repeatable nested blocks, but avoid overusing them as they can make code harder to read.
